As can be seen in the video, data is accumulated in the Arduino buffer, although in response to all the data the controller sends the correct response.
Stop occurs in a random place G-code.

http://cnc.tiven.ru/ssr-2018-12-22_18.27.31.mp4

Code arduino:
```c
void setup() {
    Serial.begin(115200);
}
void loop() {}

String inputString = "";  
void serialEvent() 
{
    while (Serial.available()) {
    char inChar = (char)Serial.read();  // get the new byte
    inputString += inChar;
    if (inChar == '\n') {
      //Serial.println(inputString);
      Serial.println("ok");
      inputString = "";
      delay(5);
      }
    }
}

```
